# File Identifier

Identify file types using **magic numbers (file signatures)** instead of file extensions.

Works even if files have incorrect or fake extensions (e.g., `.pdf.exe`).

---

## 🚀 Installation

```bash id="kgm8bt"
pip install file-identifier
```

---

## 🛠 Usage

```bash id="2r1fdn"
file-identifier <file_or_directory> [options]
```

---

### Basic

```bash id="t4w0k4"
file-identifier file.pdf
```

---

### JSON Output

```bash id="vdlm2b"
file-identifier file.pdf --json
```

---

### Detect Extension Mismatch

```bash id="2j8lq8"
file-identifier suspicious.pdf.exe
```

---

### Directory Scan

```bash id="7ng4pq"
file-identifier ./folder
```

---

### Verbose Mode

```bash id="y9c0v2"
file-identifier file.zip --verbose
```

---

## 📊 Output

* File type
* Likely extension
* File size
* Confidence level
* Hex header

---

## 🧠 How it works

Reads the first bytes of a file and matches them with known **magic signatures**.

